ed 1<b>. Transfer into simmering basket and set over a bowl to drain and cool (approx. 30 minutes)."},{"content":"Line a baking tray (30 x 40 cm) with baking paper and set aside."},{"content":"Place 1 spring roll wrapper, floured side facing up, onto a clean work surface, with one corner facing down (wrapper will look like a diamond). Cover remaining wrappers with a clean, damp kitchen towel. Form 2 tablespoons of the mixture into a sausage shape, then place horizontally onto wrapper towards bottom edge of diamond. Brush sides of wrapper with water. Fold in bottom point of diamond to enclose filling, then fold in both sides to overlap filling. Gently roll wrapper up, making sure edges are tucked inside and filling is completely sealed. Place seam side down onto prepared tray. Repeat with remaining wrappers and filling."},{"content":"Line a plate with paper towel and set aside."},{"content":"Place a large saucepan over medium heat. Add oil (approx. 8 cm high) and bring to 175°C (see Tip). Keep your oil at this temperature while frying. Working in batches, carefully place 5-6 spring rolls into oil and fry for 5 minutes or until golden in colour, keeping rolls apart during first minute of frying to prevent sticking. Using a slotted spoon, carefully remove and transfer onto prepared plate to drain. Serve spring rolls with sweet chilli sauce on the side. "}],"hintsAndTricks":["To check your oil is at 175°C, use a kitchen thermometer or drop a small cube of bread in the oil; it should turn golden in 15-20 seconds."],"basicInfo":["medium","45m","1h 10m","12 portions"]}